{"parse":{"title":"Thomas Oliver (engineer)","pageid":39292597,"revid":691363469,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p><b>Thomas Oliver</b> was an engineer who invented the first machine for forging <a href=\"/wiki/Bolt_(fastener)\" title=\"Bolt (fastener)\">bolts</a> in England.  This used a treadle-operated hammer which was called an <b>Oliver hammer</b> or <b>English Oliver</b>, after the inventor.  Production of bolts using this machinery started in <a href=\"/wiki/Darlaston\" title=\"Darlaston\">Darlaston</a> in <a href=\"/wiki/Staffordshire\" title=\"Staffordshire\">Staffordshire</a> in 1838.<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>  Similar machines were still being using in the <a href=\"/wiki/Black_Country\" title=\"Black Country\">Black Country</a> in 1979, at <a href=\"/wiki/Lench%27s_Oliver_Shop\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Lench&#39;s Oliver Shop\">Lench's Oliver Shop</a>, making special bolts to order.<sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>  Using such a hammer could be strenuous work, stamping on the treadle to force the red hot iron into the <a href=\"/wiki/Die_(manufacturing)\" title=\"Die (manufacturing)\">die</a> over a thousand times a day.  Despite the physical strain and injury which resulted, even women laboured in this way during the 19th century.<sup id=\"cite_ref-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Thomas_Oliver_(engineer)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite id=\"CITEREFFranklin_Day_Jones1928\" class=\"citation\">Franklin Day Jones (1928), <i>Handbook Encyclopedia of Engineering</i>, p.&#160;127</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Handbook+Encyclopedia+of+Engineering&amp;rft.pages=127&amp;rft.date=1928&amp;rft.au=Franklin+Day+Jones&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AThomas+Oliver+%28engineer%29\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-2\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite id=\"CITEREFE.J.Wiley1926\" class=\"citation\">E.J.Wiley (1926), \"The Development of Bolt and Nut Forging\", <i>Machinery and Production Engineering</i>, <b>29</b>: 430</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=Machinery+and+Production+Engineering&amp;rft.atitle=The+Development+of+Bolt+and+Nut+Forging&amp;rft.volume=29&amp;rft.pages=430&amp;rft.date=1926&amp;rft.au=E.J.Wiley&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AThomas+Oliver+%28engineer%29\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-3\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.bclm.co.uk/locations/lenchs-oliver-shop/12.htm#.UYQIGaKgGoS\"><i>Lench\u2019s Oliver Shop</i></a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Black_Country_Living_Museum\" title=\"Black Country Living Museum\">Black Country Living Museum</a></cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Lench%E2%80%99s+Oliver+Shop&amp;rft.pub=Black+Country+Living+Museum&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.bclm.co.uk%2Flocations%2Flenchs-oliver-shop%2F12.htm%23.UYQIGaKgGoS&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AThomas+Oliver+%28engineer%29\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-4\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-4\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation\">\"Annotations.\", <i><a href=\"/wiki/The_Lancet\" title=\"The Lancet\">The Lancet</a></i>, <b>1</b>: 498, 541, 1889, <a href=\"/wiki/Digital_object_identifier\" title=\"Digital object identifier\">doi</a>:<a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"//doi.org/10.1016/S0140-6736%2800%2949982-4\">10.1016/S0140-6736(00)49982-4</a></cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=The+Lancet&amp;rft.atitle=Annotations.&amp;rft.volume=1&amp;rft.pages=498%2C+541&amp;rft.date=1889&amp;rft_id=info%3Adoi%2F10.1016%2FS0140-6736%2800%2949982-4&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AThomas+Oliver+%28engineer%29\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n<p><br />\n</p>\n<table class=\"metadata plainlinks stub\" role=\"presentation\" style=\"background:transparent\"><tbody><tr><td><a href=\"/wiki/File:Nuvola_apps_kfig.svg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"Stub icon\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/57/Nuvola_apps_kfig.svg/30px-Nuvola_apps_kfig.svg.png\" width=\"30\" height=\"30\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/57/Nuvola_apps_kfig.svg/45px-Nuvola_apps_kfig.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/57/Nuvola_apps_kfig.svg/59px-Nuvola_apps_kfig.svg.png 2x\" data-file-width=\"109\" data-file-height=\"110\" /></a></td><td><i>This engineering-related article is a <a href=\"/wi